#install.packages("oro.nifti")
library(oro.nifti)
## oro.nifti 0.11.0
mri_image <- readNIfTI("NM_GRE_C43_CombEcho_s004.nii", reorient=FALSE)

nrows <- dim(mri_image)[1]
ncols <- dim(mri_image)[2]
nslices <- dim(mri_image)[3]


image(mri_image, z=45,plot.type="single") 

##install.packages("fslr")
library(fslr)
## Loading required package: neurobase
##bias extraction 
biascorrection <- fsl_biascorrect(mri_image,retimg = TRUE)
## Warning in get.fsl(): Setting fsl.path to /usr/local/fsl
## Warning in get.fsloutput(): Can't find FSLOUTPUTTYPE, setting to NIFTI_GZ
## FSLDIR='/usr/local/fsl'; PATH=${FSLDIR}/bin:${PATH};export PATH FSLDIR; sh "${FSLDIR}/etc/fslconf/fsl.sh"; FSLOUTPUTTYPE=NIFTI_GZ; export FSLOUTPUTTYPE; ${FSLDIR}/bin/fast    -B --nopve --out="/var/folders/6m/tsffc3c94150022y201z19hw0000gp/T//RtmpGyc6h4/filea8e52d4d705f" "/private/var/folders/6m/tsffc3c94150022y201z19hw0000gp/T/RtmpGyc6h4/filea8e5a3d09c9.nii.gz";
image(biascorrection, z=45,plot.type="single") 

##brain extraction
bet <- fslbet(infile=biascorrection,retimg = TRUE)
## FSLDIR='/usr/local/fsl'; PATH=${FSLDIR}/bin:${PATH};export PATH FSLDIR; sh "${FSLDIR}/etc/fslconf/fsl.sh"; FSLOUTPUTTYPE=NIFTI_GZ; export FSLOUTPUTTYPE; ${FSLDIR}/bin/bet2 "/private/var/folders/6m/tsffc3c94150022y201z19hw0000gp/T/RtmpGyc6h4/filea8e516bbcfcf.nii.gz" "/var/folders/6m/tsffc3c94150022y201z19hw0000gp/T//RtmpGyc6h4/filea8e5370c8435"
image(bet)

FSLDIR='/usr/local/fsl'
library(neurobase)
### brain segmentation
extract <- fast(bet)
## FSLDIR='/usr/local/fsl'; PATH=${FSLDIR}/bin:${PATH};export PATH FSLDIR; sh "${FSLDIR}/etc/fslconf/fsl.sh"; FSLOUTPUTTYPE=NIFTI_GZ; export FSLOUTPUTTYPE; ${FSLDIR}/bin/fast  --verbose --out="/var/folders/6m/tsffc3c94150022y201z19hw0000gp/T//RtmpGyc6h4/filea8e51deb0e50" "/private/var/folders/6m/tsffc3c94150022y201z19hw0000gp/T/RtmpGyc6h4/filea8e54482ab2.nii.gz";
library(scales)

ortho2(bet,extract==2,col.y=alpha("red",0.5),text="Grey Matter")

ortho2(bet,extract==3,col.y=alpha("white",0.5),text="White Matter")

ortho2(bet,extract==1,col.y=alpha("blue",0.5),text="Cerebrospinal Fluid")
